"'''Retreat from Coruscant'''" is a short story written by [[Laurie Burns]]. It originally appeared in [[Star Wars Adventure Journal 7|''Star Wars Adventure Journal'' 7]] by [[West End Games]] in August [[1995]] and was later reprinted in the short-story anthology ''[[Tales from the Empire]]'', which was published by [[Bantam Spectra]] in November [[1997]].

==Plot summary==
Shortly before the events of ''[[Star Wars: Dark Empire]]'' in [[10 ABY/Legends|10 ABY]], [[Courier/Legends|courier]] [[Freighter/Legends|freighter]] [[Captain/Legends|captain]] [[Taryn Clancy]] and her ship, the [[Messenger (starship)|''Messenger'']], are trapped beneath the [[Planetary shield/Legends|planetary shields]] of [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]] when the reinvigorated [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] forces attack the capital. The [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] signals a full-scale evacuation of the [[Ecumenopolis/Legends|city-planet]]. [[General/Legends|General]] [[Garm Bel Iblis/Legends|Garm Bel Iblis]] commandeers Taryn's ship, appointing [[Colonel/Legends|Colonel]] [[Jak Bremen]] to serve aboard as Taryn must deliver vital information to the [[New Republic Defense Fleet/Legends|New Republic fleet]]. Avoiding Imperial pursuit and bluffing her way past an Imperial inspection, Taryn succeeds in delivering a secure message regarding a new rendezvous point to the fleet. 

